Find the parent nodes of leaf nodes in a hierarchical tree structure represented as a list of dictionaries in Python.
Input: nodes = [
    {"name": "a", "children": [{"name": "b"}, {"name": "c"}]},
    {"name": "b", "children": [{"name": "d"}]},
    {"name": "c", "children": []},
    {"name": "d", "children": []}
]

Required Output: [
  {'name': 'c', 'parent': {'name': 'a'}}, 
  {'name': 'd', 'parent': {'name': 'a', 'parent': {'name': 'b'}}}
]
